FBIS3-7456 "dreas060_c_94018" FBIS-EAS-94-060 Document Type:Daily Report 28 Mar 1994 North Korea Lebanese Party Leader Sends Solidarity Message OW2803073094 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0508 GMT 28 Mar 94 OW2803073094 Pyongyang KCNA Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Pyongyang, March 28 (KCNA) -- The Great Leader President Kim Il-song received a solidarity message from Walid Junblatt, chairman of the Socialist Progressive Party of Lebanon, supporting Korean people's struggle to defend the country's sovereignty. The message dated March 24 notes that the situation of the Korean peninsula has been extremely strained by continued pressure of the United States against the DPRK. It says: We extend full support to and solidarity with the Korean people in their struggle to defend the country's sovereignty under the outstanding guidance of President Kim Il-song. We hope Korean reunification will be realized at an early date in accordance with the 10-point programme of the Great Unity of the Whole Nation set forth by President Kim Il-song, and express the conviction that this will greatly contribute to removing the tensions and achieving peace in Asia and the rest of the world.
